Dialogs.Dialog: Yeah... right now, it is still outside of Rinko's active hours.
Just a little. I bought a new game, but I was having trouble defeating the boss. When I came to, it was bright outside.
But isn't that better than seeing a grumpy Rinko without being able to beat the boss？ Thanks to that, Rinko is smiling today.
Hey, don't you think all classes should be in the afternoon？
That's out of the blue. What about in the morning？
I'd like to take a break and relax in the mornings. I'm sure everyone will agree.
But then you'd have to stay up all night for classes, wouldn't you？
...better not. I want to relax at least at night.
(Huh, I can see you there, ▲小早川＊▲...)
What's up, you look gloomy, ▲小早川＊▲.
You, a no-nonsense person, wouldn't get it.
...is it really that serious of a concern？
Yeah, the teacher got mad at me for being late so much. Hah...
Hah... I've got PE in the morning... give me a break. My body hasn't woken up yet.
Yeah, I wish it was still in the afternoon.
Afternoon is afternoon, and after lunch, you get sleepy.
When is a good time for you？
Hmmm... when Rinko feels like it？
Sorry, did I bump into you, ▲小早川＊▲！？
I was doing squats in PE... and I got kind of pissed off. Then...
Oh, hey, hey. I saw some green juice at the store a while ago, why is it there？
Why is it there, you ask... isn't it a request from someone？
...that doesn't taste like something a high school student would drink.
I have, but I'm telling you, Rinko doesn't think is that good. It's just bitter.
(I don't think I'd drink if you told me that much.)
Yo, you going to the library？ At this hour？
Yeah, I went to pick up something I forgot, ▲主人公＊▲.
I see. Well, do you want some company？
Why... I don't have a reason to.
What are you doing here, ▲小早川＊▲？
Training. If there's a bad guy... I'll punch him.
...I'm just kidding. Why would you take it so seriously？
I really though you would, ▲小早川＊▲.
...you know, I'll do that right away.
I only do it for you. It's an expression of love.
Ah, geez... I was looking for you.
What can I do for you？
Nothing now. I was going to ask you to help me carry the materials, but I gave up.
I don't think it's good to give up on that.
Rinko Kobayakawa, 1st year student, please come to the staff room ASAP.
It's funny looking down from the rooftop, people look like ants.
You seem to be trying to say something... What？
I was just hanging around and I just kind of thought of it. Why that one, ▲小早川＊▲？
...I thought I'd practice my basketball skills. I didn't want to embarrass myself during gym class... ah, geez, I didn't think I'd be seen.
We met at a good place. You know, don't you think it's not fair to catch me by surprise, ▲主人公＊▲？
Nope. I was in a math class, and we had an unannounced quiz...
Ah, so that's why it was a mess.
Don't assume, though, it's right. Even Rinko would have done her homework if she'd known in advance.
You are not wrong, but it's not what you think it is.
I came here today to be praised. Rinko wrote a book review in the library newsletter and they said it was very well received, and asked me if I would like to write a serialized version.
Well, it's a hassle, so I'm not going to serialize it. I don't feel like doing it.
(If you do, I would read it ▲小早川＊▲.)
Your remembering laughter is a little creepy, ▲小早川＊▲...
Oh, don't listen to me without permission. I'm about to do a chemistry experiment.
I thought you weren't good at science at all, ▲小早川＊▲？
Experiments are different. It's easy, and it's pretty fun.
(I'm guessing that doesn't reflect in your grades.)
Are you in a bad mood, ▲小早川＊▲？
Today, I overslept and didn't eat breakfast... I'm still waiting for lunch.
If you have your lunch early...？
I can't do that kind of athletic boy thing.
I don't know about that analogy, but you're hungry, right？
It's okay, it's not aesthetically pleasing.
You look sleepy as usual, ▲小早川＊▲.
I don't do that usually. I can't help it now, I've been hypnotized.
Math class. The teacher's way of speaking is so intense that Rinko's class calls him "the hypnotist".
It's dangerous, especially in the afternoon classes. It's force majeure, you see.
What's wrong, are you sick, or are you injured, ▲小早川＊▲？
There's no need to be in such a panic. It's just a nap.
Yeah. I'm so glad to see you, and I'm wide awake, too.
(Too！ My ass... you really surprised me...)
This is your favorite spot ▲小早川＊▲？
Yeah, it's hard to breathe when you're in a classroom.
It's not like something happened... I hope.
Nothing happened. Don't worry. Do you want some juice？
If you don't want it, fine.
(It's an indirect kiss... but it's okay.)
You seem to be zoning out, ▲小早川＊▲.
Just a little. In the afternoon, you start to wonder if it's going to be after school soon.
But if you're so carefree, they'll get mad at you in class.
I know that. Honestly, you're so preachy.
I'm going to take my classes. What should I do after class today？
What are you doing here, ▲小早川＊▲？
I was just passing by, but look, aren't the human body models in the science lab kinda nice, ▲主人公＊▲？
I don't get it at all！
Yeah, Rinko can't use the classroom right now, ▲主人公＊▲.
It's like the boys have invented another silly game. Things are flying around, and I can't even read.
That's right, old man. But really, they're like grade schoolers.
Hey, hey. There' s a new drink in the school cafeteria.
Even if there's an add, it's probably just another tea or something anyway, right？
I hear there's some kind of kiwi stuff, you're curious, right？
Rinko is curious. So, you know, be a human sacrifice. Okay？
You know, do you enjoy club activities？ When I saw you doing it, I got kind of interested.
Heh. Well, why don't you try out for a club somewhere？
Well... maybe a gaming club？ We go to the arcade on the club's dime.
So I guess I'll just have to make it. It's a pain in the ass...
Be assured that it will never happen.
Don't you have a funny nickname？
A nickname？ Why do you ask all of a sudden.
(Did they give you a funny nickname？)
Why would that be. I just saw you...
So you want to go with me to the girls' locker room？
You want to join the club ▲小早川＊▲？
I was passing by here and the tennis club advisor told me to clean the courts. What does that mean？
Oh... I think Suzuki-sensei mistook you, maybe？
Hah, what's with that. Then you, a member of the club, should do it for me.
Well, then, that's what we're going to do.
Are you involved in any class activities？
I don't have a class rep. I'm on the Library Committee.
My homeroom teacher asked me to do it. Why would they ask Rinko, who is very busy, to do it？
It looks like a cat came this way, so I chased after it, but I lost it, ▲主人公＊▲.
Heh, well, why don't you call it？ Nya, like that.
Yeah, I guess so. I'm not going to say nya...
There's a lot of noise, do you know what's going on, ▲小早川＊▲？
I heard that a dog came in earlier and took a cutlet sandwich from the cafeteria.
What, a dog made it to the school building？ Are you okay with that...
It's okay. I saw the dog. It was a mini-dachshund. It belonged to a client who came to the school.
I see, so that was it.
Hehe, it was cute. Dogs are pretty good too.
Oh... I'm okay, I've been reading a little bit of fiction. It's a series called "Puzzled by the Night".
It would be embarrassing if I cried when I read it in class.
...that's cold, are you mad at me？
Rinko has few time to spare, so if you don't need me, I'll see you later.
Eh, is there something wrong？ If there's anything I can do――
Geez, shut up. I forgot my homework and have to do it in a hurry.
What are you mumbling about ▲小早川＊▲？
Ah... it's you. Say, Rinko's face today looks kinda weird, doesn't it？
It's the same as usual. You're cute.
Hah！？ I'm not sure what to say here！ ...I guess you can't ask a guy.
(Is there some difference that only she can tell？)
Eh, oh... you know, there are schools where orange juice comes out of the faucet at the water fountain.
But I was wondering how you wash your hands... It'll be gooey in the end.
...there's a faucet with water coming out of it to wash it, right？
I see, you also get water... I get it. Ah, that's clarifying.
(No way, that's what you were worried about...)
Day or night, when I wake up, my greeting is good morning. What's the problem？
(You're in a bad mood when you wake up from sleep, whether it's in the morning or at noon...)
Oh, you want to hear it？ You know, Fumiko Midou's new book is coming out.
It's Ms. Fumiko Midou, a giant star in the shoujo manga world！ If you don't know her works, you're missing out on 80% of your life.
(The I'm just living at a 20% then...)
What's up？ Did the sensei get mad at you again, ▲小早川＊▲？
A mechanical pencil in the shape of a cat's tail is missing... ah, geez, this is the worst.
If the pen has such a feature, you can find it.
Courtyards are so nice, aren't they, ▲小早川＊▲？
Yeah, it's nice to hang around here.
Makes you wish this time could go on forever, doesn't it？
Hah, here it is. I have to go back to class.
Class is about to start, ▲小早川＊▲.
Rinko's class is self- study. I saw your class doing P.E., so I snuck out for a bit.
...if they find out, they'll be pissed.
Well, when it comes to classes, it's like they make you do it all at once, ▲小早川＊▲.
Yes, especially choral singing. You don't want to sing a song you don't like.
You like to be here, right, ▲小早川＊▲？
...yeah. Being here reminds me of a lot of things.
Oh... no！ I didn't mean that one！ It doesn't make any difference though...
Ah, geez, I don't want to keep talking about this！
That's okay, just a little bit.
Not a little, not a lot. It's like we're flirting with the people around us.
Huh, did you come to borrow a book, too？
Hmm, I just kind of came here. Since I'm here, I guess I'll ask you for a recommendation, ▲小早川＊▲.
We don't have any erotic books.
Is that so？ Then I don't have a recommendation for you.
Don't say those kinds of things...
Hey, why don't humans have paw pads？ If we had them, we could tickle them in our spare time, and they're cute, right？
Hmm... it's not cute even if you have paw pads on you... it's rather scary. It's fine then.
Heh... you have that kind of fetish？
(Don't say that in a weird way...)
Whoa！？ Why are you under the counter？
I saw you coming, so I thought I'd surprise you. How did it go？
If you ask me how it was, I'd say... childish.
...oh, here comes the good part. Piggyback.
I've been dealing with loaners all day, so I'm tired. So give me a piggyback ride to the classroom.
...I've got no choice. I'll do it because you ask me, ▲小早川＊▲.
...it was a joke, but... hehe, I see, you can do it if I ask you to.
Hey, did you hear they're strengthening the science section next time？
Oh... I remember hearing something like that.
I was asked to list the books... but I'm not sure about it.
Yay！ I knew I could count on my boyfriend.
(If they're this happy, how can I not help？)
Say, have you ever wanted to live in a library？
If you ask me if I want to live there... I'm not sure.
Rinko wants to live here permanently. Because you can read all you want, right？
Instead, I'm on book duty every day.
...I'll give up on living there permanently, I'll do a homestay instead.
(You want to stay in for a few days.)
Huh？ I thought she was on duty, but... you skipped it again, ▲小早川＊▲.
What am I doing, you ask... of course I'm reading a book in the library.
(You're curled up under the counter reading... like a little animal...)
Say, why are committee heads so picky about the rules？
Hah. Generally speaking, with Mitsuami glasses... what are the rules and regulations？
Mitsuami glasses？ Our chairman is neither Mitsuami nor uses glasses.
Really？ That's how it looks to Rinko, sort of.
I thought you were on library duty, ▲小早川＊▲？
There were no users today, no one.
Just because no one is there doesn't mean you can skip out.
It's okay. I'll be back when someone comes.
...how would you know that someone is coming？
It's, you know, the Library Committee member's intuition.
Hah... I have to choose a recommendation for the library newsletter by the end of this week.
You're good at that, right, ▲小早川＊▲？
I'm running out of stories. I know that Rinko's favorite book is not for everyone.
It would be interesting to have something like that once in a while. Let's say you're in charge, ▲小早川＊▲.
We're in trouble. Factional fights are going to start among the Library Committee members.
That's the first time I've ever heard you talk about that. I thought everyone was close.
It's a blood feud between the entertainment group and the pure literature group. Rinko is more on the side of pure literature...
Ah, so those were the factions...
Of course it is. What did you think it was？
(Fight over the next head of the committee... something like that.)
I've finally solved the mystery. The mystery of the library.
Flowers on the rental counter. You couldn't always tell who was arranging them, could you？

It seems it was the work of the chairman. It's a tradition that has been handed down from generation to generation by the chairman of the Library Committee. It's like a secret handed down from one generation to the next.
(So... a parable on how to live？)
Hey, something seems to be wrong with the computer.
Yeah, it's been that way for a while now. I'd love to have a new one.
I hear it's hard to ask for a new one. Hmm, anyway, I wonder if I can borrow one from the staff room.
Borrowing, huh... Oh, you mean asking to borrow it.
Eh？ Uh, oh, yeah. Formal request. Yeah, because it's an emergency.
(Didn't you think you could borrow... without permission, right？)
Ah, just in time. I've been asked to write a feature article for the next issue of the library newsletter, do you have any stories？
Even if you ask me... the last time I was here, it was a light novel feature, and the time before that, it was...
That was too heavily weighted toward cats, and you were warned.
Of course that's what happens when you put Rinko in charge. But the readers loved it, remember？
The last time I had a vendor pick up my old books, I was a little sad.
I get you... because the committee members repaired the books.
...I hope they can find a new owner.
Why would someone not meet the return deadline？
...I guess they just forget about it. I'm sure people don't mean to offend you.
If you can get away with no offense, you don't need the police.
It's a new book and it's been overdue for a week, you know how much Rinko is looking forward to it. Ah, geez...
(Please, give it back to her as soon as possible...)
I was just asked by the teacher to dry out the books in the stacks.
Perhaps even that burly encyclopedia-like book？
Yes, it's a show of your strength as a man, and your girlfriend might fall back in love with you.
Kya, you're so cool. I'm going to love you even more.
Eh？ Did I promise you something？
I asked you to help me organize the new books after school...
Eh... you didn't ask me, did you？
Eh？ ...Oh, I tried to tell you during lunch break and forgot. Hehe, sorry.
It's obvious at a glance. What are you going to do about it？
What do you want me to do... you're just grumpy.
The rain. Rinko doesn't like the watery air.
Good morning... That's the first thing you say in the morning？
Because it's raining, you're going to get wet.
Even with an umbrella, if you get wet, you get wet！
Is it going to rain all day today？
Hah. I'm not good with rain. I wouldn't go to school if I were alone.
Don't try to take a day off just because it's raining...
Nice weather, isn't it？ I hope it stays that way.
I don't know. It'll be fine, isn't it？
I hope it stays that way.
Too many clouds？ I have a bad feeling about this...
I don't want to get rained on along the way.
Cloudy, huh？ Well, I guess it's okay.
It might be easier to spend time at home.
It's raining, what are you going to do about it？
Rain, huh... well, it can't be helped.
It can't be helped. Come on, let's go.
You know... Rinko's looking forward to it.
...I meant our date！ Did you make me say that on purpose？
It's not like that. I'm looking forward to it too.
I didn't say that. Well, expectations are normal.
(She's late... Well, I'll wait for you a longer, ▲小早川＊▲...)
ought I was ahead of you... I thought you were going to be late too.
I wouldn't leave you. Look, if you hurry a little, you can make it.
You're just acting cool... Thanks, though.
If you know Rinko is waiting for you, why are you late？
Sorry... my alarm clock didn't go off...
Huh？ Do I need an English- Japanese dictionary today？
Don't ask me... If you forget, I'll lend it to you.
(You could have just asked for a loan honestly...)
Sorry, Rinko is going after it！
Hey now, don't chase after it！ We're gonna be late！
What's the matter？ Did you forget something？
I forgot to put my newly purchased song in the player. I think I'll go back and put it in....
You're going to be late, you should hold off for at least one day.
I have a bento... do you want some？
Sure, I'll eat！ Um, for the place...
Today I have prepared a bento. I prepared one for you, too, you know？
Really？ Then where shall we eat？
I made a bento for you.
Oh, thank you. Where shall we eat？
Do you want to eat at the ▲飲食店＊＊＊＊＊▲？
Do you want to go to the ▲飲食店＊＊＊＊＊▲？
I didn't brought a bento today.
Okay. So you want to go to the cafeteria？
Hmm, I don't remember us ever going together. Well, let's do that.
I didn't brought a bento today, what should we do？
Hmm... so how about the school cafeteria？ We've never been together, have we？
That sounds good. Let's do that.
I didn't brought a bento today...
So why don't we go to the cafeteria？ You haven't gone with me yet.
I'm in the mood for a school lunch today.
I'm going to the cafeteria today.
The school cafeteria, huh. That's a good idea too.
Listen, I want to go to the cafeteria today. Is that okay？
I think it was pretty good.
Hmm. So you don't need Rinko's bento anymore？
Ah, I see. It can't be helped.
Thanks for the food. That was good！
It wasn't as good as your bento, you know, ▲小早川＊▲！
Yes, yes, keep up the good work. I'll make you another one.
Phew, I may have eaten too much.
Keep it to eight portions. You'll get sleepy.
I'm getting sleepy... can I sleep here？
After I told you. I told you not to go to sleep！
I'm lucky to have an umbrella
I don't want to get wet, glad I have it.
Do you have an umbrella, ▲主人公＊▲？
Yeah, no problem. Don't you have one ▲小早川＊▲？
I didn't bring it, after all. Let me in.
Shall we go home together, ▲小早川＊▲？
Sure. Do you have an umbrella？
I'm glad to hear that. It wouldn't feel good to send one person home soaking wet.
We can be together under one...
It's a hassle, I should run home...
Are you going home without an umbrella？ It's not possible, you know, ▲主人公＊▲.
I think I can make if I run ▲小早川＊▲.
Don't act cool, and get under Rinko's umbrella.
It can't be helped. If you catch a cold, Rinko will have a boring time.
Ugh, it's raining pretty hard... well, okay, let's run.
Hey, are you hungry？ I know you are.
We had a cooking class, so I made some pastries. You'll try some, won't you？
What do you think？ I don't have to ask.
(You're so confident. Yes, this tastes good！)
It should not be a failure.
I wish I could have made it taste better...
Before I go any further, let me tell you, you don't have to do this.
I didn't have any bad intentions.
(Ugh... even if you didn't, this taste...)
Sorry. I'm not really confident about it...
You're drooling. Don't just dawdle, get up quickly.
You came to wake me up. But I'm still sleepy, ▲小早川＊▲.
Are you going to make me wait any longer？ Rinko did her best to get up very early to come here.
I see... thank you. I'll get up...
Hey... what are you talking about！
Ah, you came for me...？ Good morning, ▲小早川＊▲.
What, you were sleep- talking... Just get up or I'll kick you！
Why are you so grumpy in the morning？
Oh, you woke up. I was going to crawl under the covers.
You are her to wake me up, ▲小早川＊▲？
Because you're the only one who fell asleep looking comfortable. It's not fair.
We are going to be late... I'm glad I woke up.
Just in time. Good for you.
(I wonder what she was going to do when she got to 0...)
Whoa！ ...don't shout in my ear, ▲小早川＊▲.
Because you don't wake up at all. Rinko's not free, you know.
My bad. You're waking me up in the morning.
Well, it's okay. You're awake, right？
Oh, it's okay. I'd better get ready quickly.
Good morning. I've been waiting for you.
Hey... did you just hear something？
Who knows, isn't it just your imagination？ Don't dawdle, get ready to go.
Hmm, why does it smell so yummy...？
You woke up at a good time.
Did you come to wake me up ▲小早川＊▲？
I made breakfast for you. The rice is freshly cooked, so let's eat it soon.
Nice！ Thank you. Did you make it Japanese food to match？
Well, maybe... look, stop grinning and get up quickly.
Wake up！ Breakfast is ready, okay？
Good morning... I like it. Feels like we're a married couple, right？
Idiot. Hurry up, or your rice will get cold.
How do you like it？ Isn't it the perfect amount of water？
Yeah. You cooked this rice so delicious...
At any rate, I think it's taking shape...
I'm happy enough just to be able to eat rice in the morning.
I think I screwed up a little bit... you can leave it.
I'm glad you made it, I'll try it...
Waking up at the smell of food, you really are a lucky man.
Well, yes. I guess I'm okay with Western food.
You even made it to my taste. You're so sweet, ▲小早川＊▲...
Hehe, you're lucky to have a witty girlfriend, aren't you？
(You're the best girlfriend I've ever had！)
Look, look, it's Rinko's homemade breakfast.
Hehe, you're a lucky boyfriend. Let's have breakfast together.
I think I did a good job, this time.
How's the taste？ I don't think it's that bad.
Yeah, I think you're doing it right.
I may have missed it at the end... What do you think？
By the way, have you decided what you are going to have for dinner today？ If you want, I can make it.
Hey, are you going home now？
Yeah, you want to go home with me, ▲小早川＊▲？
Yeah. So... have you decided what you want to eat for dinner tonight？ Do you want Rinko to make it for you？
Hey, for today's dinner... how about Rinko goes and cooks it, so we eat it together？
Hehe, that's the way to do it. Let's go to the supermarket then.
Right. Let's go buy some ingredients.
This supermarket carries some pretty unusual foods.
What's on sale today？ There's nothing better than a low price.
Shopping together side by side like this... is nice, right？
By the way, what do you want to eat？
I'm in the mood for ▲メニュー▲.
Then I can count on you.
Okay, I guess I can handle it then.
Hmmm... well, I'll give it a try.
Well, it'll be all right, isn't it？
Now that we've decided that, let's get the ingredients together.
That's everything, right？ I hope we didn't forget to buy anything.
If you forget, I'll run out to buy it. Now, let's go home.
It was quite a task because we had a lot of baggage.
Good job, he says... the real work is just beginning.
I bet your luggage was heavy, wasn't it？ Thanks for your hard work.
I think this is the first time you came to prepare dinner for me, ▲小早川＊▲.
Right, you can be grateful for that, okay？ Hehe.
Well, feel free to come on in.
Well, then, I will be happy to come in.
Haha, it's like your own house.
Well. I'm going to make this with a lot of energy, so don't get in Rinko's way.
Then I'll start making it, just wait a minute.
I knew it would be nice to have dinner together. Thank you for today's meal.
Okay, I'll give you a lift, let's go...
No need. I'm fine on my own... See you.
Thank you for the food. The food was delicious and we had a lot of fun.
Well, I'd be happy to make it again if it's this good.
Well then, I'll take you home now for the day.
It's fine. I can go home alone... Bye-bye.
Thanks for the food. It made me happy.
Rinko had fun too. I'll make it again.
That's okay, Rinko can go home alone. I'll see you later.
I'll better send it to you.
Hey, did I ever say this... Rinko keeps a diary.
I thought you would say that. It's fine.
It's not bad. What kind of things are you writing？
(Hmm, I do wonder what you write about in your diary, ▲小早川＊▲...)
